Execute only PHASE 10.1.

Goal:
Add Phase 10 billing model foundation and default plan catalog.

Create/update:
backend/app/billing/__init__.py
backend/app/billing/models.py
backend/app/billing/plan_catalog.py
backend/app/db/models.py
backend/app/db/repositories.py
backend/app/core/config.py
.env.example

Tests:
backend/app/tests/test_billing_models.py
backend/app/tests/test_plan_catalog.py

Config additions:
BILLING_ENABLED=true
BILLING_PROVIDER=mock
BILLING_CURRENCY=USD
BILLING_TRIAL_DAYS=14
BILLING_GRACE_PERIOD_DAYS=7
BILLING_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
BILLING_FAIL_CLOSED=true

STRIPE_ENABLED=false
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
STRIPE_PRICE_STARTER=
STRIPE_PRICE_PRO=
STRIPE_PRICE_ENTERPRISE=

Rules:
- Mock billing must work without provider secrets.
- Real Stripe mode requires all required Stripe config.
- Billing must fail closed when BILLING_FAIL_CLOSED=true.
- Do not store raw card data.
- Do not hardcode payment provider secrets.
- All billing data tenant-scoped by organization_id and workspace_id where applicable.
- SQLite and PostgreSQL compatible.
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.x style where touching database models.
- Preserve existing billing code if scaffold exists; harden/complete instead of replacing blindly.

Billing models:
1. PlanTier:
   free, starter, pro, enterprise

2. SubscriptionStatus:
   trialing, active, past_due, canceled, expired, suspended

3. BillingPlan:
   id, tier, name, description, price_monthly, price_yearly, currency, features, limits, is_public, created_at, updated_at

4. Subscription:
   id, organization_id, plan_id, status, provider, provider_customer_id, provider_subscription_id,
   trial_ends_at, current_period_start, current_period_end, cancel_at_period_end, metadata, created_at, updated_at

5. UsageRecord:
   id, organization_id, workspace_id, metric, quantity, source, resource_id, metadata, measured_at, created_at

6. UsageSummary:
   organization_id, workspace_id, metric, used, limit, remaining, reset_at, percent_used

7. Invoice:
   id, organization_id, provider, provider_invoice_id, status, amount_due, amount_paid, currency,
   hosted_invoice_url, invoice_pdf_url, created_at, due_at, paid_at

8. EntitlementDecision:
   allowed, feature, reason, plan_tier, required_tier, quota, usage, timestamp

